--- HELLO.PAS ---
{$D-,L-,A+,R-,S-}
USES
  WinCRT;
BEGIN
  Writeln('Hello World!');
END.

compiles to HELLO.EXE (8448 bytes)
Using Delphi's W8LOSS utility on HELLO.EXE reduce the size to 7905 bytes.

How on earth you got a 150K .EXE, beats me!

